articles.author: Rollo Ross, Jackie Luna
articles.description: Wildfires raged deep into the storied heartland of the American film industry.
articles.title: Hollywood Hills burn as LA engulfed by 'the big one'

articles.author: Vivian Sequera, Mircely Guanipa
articles.description: Venezuelan opposition parties and their supporters were holding protests around the country on Thursday in an eleventh-hour effort to put pressure on President Nicolas Maduro, one day before he is due to be sworn in for his third six-year term.
articles.title: As Maduro inauguration looms, Venezuela opposition hold street protests

articles.author: Hyunjoo Jin, Hyonhee Shin
articles.description: South Korean President Yoon Suk Yeol's security chief said on Friday the impeached leader, who faces arrest over a criminal probe into his Dec. 3 martial law bid, has been unfairly treated for a sitting leader and warned bloodshed must be avoided.
articles.title: South Korea presidential security chief warns against violent attempt to arrest Yoon

articles.author: Daren Butler, Ece Toksabay, Umit Ozdal
articles.description: Talks aimed at ending a 40-year-old militant conflict have fostered peace hopes in Turkey but the precarious situation of Kurdish forces in Syria and uncertainty about Ankara's intentions have left many Kurds anxious about the path ahead.
articles.title: Efforts to end Kurdish militant conflict in Turkey face Syria test

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Austrian Foreign Minister Alexander Schallenberg was sworn in as caretaker chancellor on Friday, succeeding fellow conservative Karl Nehammer who quit last weekend after his attempt to form a centrist coalition government without the far right failed.
articles.title: Austrian foreign minister Schallenberg takes over as caretaker chancellor

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Russia accused Ukraine on Friday of carrying out a missile strike on a supermarket in the Russian-controlled city of Donetsk in eastern Ukraine, saying the attack killed two civilians and wounded two others.
articles.title: Russia accuses Ukraine of striking supermarket in Donetsk, killing two

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Israel confirmed that a hostage found killed in Gaza was Hamza Ziyadne, the son of another hostage, Youssef Ziyadne, found dead alongside him in an underground tunnel near the southern city of Rafah.
articles.title: Israeli military confirms identity of Israeli hostage killed in Gaza

articles.author: Dmitry Antonov
articles.description: Russia welcomes the stated willingness of U.S. President-elect Donald Trump to resolve problems through dialogue, Kremlin spokesman Dmitry Peskov said on Friday, reaffirming Russian President Vladimir Putin's readiness for talks with Trump.
articles.title: Russia says it welcomes Trump's readiness to solve problems through dialogue

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Japanese Foreign Minister Takeshi Iwaya will travel to South Korea on Monday to shore up security cooperation between the East Asian neighbours and their mutual U.S. ally that is meant to counter China's growing regional power.
articles.title: Japan foreign minister to visit S.Korea to shore up security cooperation

articles.author: Reuters
articles.description: Medical aid agency MSF said on Friday it has been forced to suspend its activities at one of the few remaining hospitals in southern Khartoum due to repeated attacks, cutting off yet another lifeline for those who remain in the Sudanese capital.
articles.title: MSF suspends operations at key hospital in Sudan's capital
